(42, 4, 15, 40, 4, 23, 23, NULL, 'Teaching in Synagogues Connection', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus teaching in synagogues, highlighting his role as a teacher in the community. Additionally, the mention of being glorified in Luke suggests a positive reception similar to the healing and preaching in Matthew.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 4, 15, 40, 9, 8, 8, 'glorified of all', 'Connection of Glory and Power', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of glorification. In Luke, Jesus is glorified by all for his teaching, while in Matthew, the multitudes glorify God for the power given to men. This connection highlights the response of people to divine authority.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 4, 15, 23, 55, 5, 5, 'glorified of all', 'Connection of Glory in Ministry', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of being glorified. In Luke, Jesus is glorified in his teaching, while Isaiah speaks of nations running to the glorified one, highlighting a shared focus on divine recognition.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 4, 15, 41, 1, 27, 27, 'being glorified of all', 'Authority in Teaching', 'This connection highlights the authority with which Jesus teaches, as seen in both passages. In Luke, he is glorified for his teaching, while in Mark, the amazement of the people stems from his authoritative command over unclean spirits.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 4, 15, 41, 1, 39, 39, 'taught in their synagogues', 'Teaching and Preaching in Galilee', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' activity in synagogues, highlighting his role as a teacher and preacher. The mention of synagogues in both verses connects their themes of Jesus'' ministry in Galilee.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 4, 15, 42, 13, 10, 10, 'taught in their synagogues', 'Teaching in Synagogues', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' role as a teacher in synagogues. The mention of teaching in both contexts highlights his active ministry and the reception he received.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 4, 15, 42, 4, 16, 16, 'taught in their synagogues', 'Jesus'' Teaching in Synagogues', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' role as a teacher in synagogues. In Luke 4:15, he is glorified for his teaching, and in Luke 4:16, he continues this practice in Nazareth, highlighting his commitment to teaching on the Sabbath.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 4, 16, 40, 2, 23, 23, 'Nazareth', 'Connection between Nazareth references', 'Both passages emphasize Nazareth as a significant location in Jesus'' life. Luke highlights Jesus'' upbringing in Nazareth, while Matthew connects this to a prophetic fulfillment regarding his identity as a Nazarene.', 'prophecy', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 4, 16, 44, 13, 14, 16, 'synagogue on the sabbath day', 'Sabbath Day Synagogue Attendance', 'Both passages emphasize the practice of attending the synagogue on the sabbath day. This connection highlights the continuity of Jewish worship and the significance of scripture reading in both Jesus'' and Paul''s ministries.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 4, 16, 44, 17, 2, 2, 'on the sabbath day', 'Sabbath Day Practices', 'This connection highlights the practice of attending synagogue on the Sabbath, as both Jesus and Paul are depicted engaging in this custom. Both passages emphasize the importance of the Sabbath for teaching and reasoning from the scriptures.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 4, 16, 40, 13, 54, 55, 'went into the synagogue on the sabbath day', 'Jesus'' Teaching in Synagogue', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' presence in the synagogue, highlighting his role as a teacher in his hometown. The astonishment of the people in Matthew reflects their recognition of his upbringing in Nazareth, as noted in Luke.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 4, 16, 41, 6, 1, 3, 'went into the synagogue on the sabbath day', 'Jesus Teaching in Synagogue', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus teaching in the synagogue on the Sabbath. This connection highlights his role as a teacher in his hometown, where he faced astonishment and offense from the locals.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 4, 16, 42, 2, 51, 51, 'Nazareth', 'Jesus'' Life in Nazareth', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' upbringing in Nazareth. In Luke 4:16, he returns to the synagogue, while Luke 2:51 highlights his submission to his parents there.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 4, 16, 42, 2, 42, 42, 'as his custom was', 'Jesus'' Custom of Reading', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' adherence to customs. In Luke 4:16, he reads in the synagogue, while in Luke 2:42, he participates in the feast custom. This connection highlights his consistent engagement with religious practices.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 4, 17, 23, 61, 1, 3, NULL, 'Connection of Anointing and Mission', 'This connection highlights the theme of anointing for a mission. Both passages emphasize the role of the Spirit and the purpose of bringing good news and healing.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 4, 17, 44, 13, 15, 15, NULL, 'Reading of Scripture in Worship', 'Both passages emphasize the reading of Scripture in a communal setting. In Luke, Jesus reads from the prophet Esaias, while in Acts, the rulers invite exhortation after the reading of the law and prophets.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 4, 17, 44, 7, 42, 42, NULL, 'Connection of Prophetic Writings', 'Both passages emphasize the use of prophetic writings. Luke references the book of the prophet Esaias, while Acts mentions ''the book of the prophets,'' linking them through their focus on prophetic scripture.', 'quotation', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 4, 17, 42, 20, 42, 42, NULL, 'Connection of Prophetic Authority', 'This connection highlights the theme of prophetic authority in both passages. In Luke 4:17, Jesus reads from Isaiah, establishing his role as a prophet, while in Luke 20:42, David''s words in the Psalms affirm the authority of the Lord''s message.', 'theme', 0.3, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 4, 17, 44, 13, 27, 27, NULL, 'Connection of Prophetic Fulfillment', 'Both passages emphasize the role of prophets in relation to Jesus. Luke highlights the reading of the prophet Esaias, while Acts notes the rulers'' failure to recognize the prophets'' voices, indicating a continuity in prophetic testimony about Jesus.', 'theme', 0.3, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 4, 18, 19, 146, 7, 8, 'to heal the brokenhearted', 'Connection of Healing and Liberation', 'Both passages emphasize healing and liberation for the oppressed. Luke 4:18 speaks of healing the brokenhearted and setting captives free, while Psalms 146:7-8 mentions loosening prisoners and opening the eyes of the blind.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 4, 18, 23, 61, 1, 1, 'the Spirit of the Lord is upon me', 'Connection of Anointing and Mission', 'Both passages emphasize the anointing of the Spirit to deliver good news and heal the brokenhearted. They share similar themes of preaching to the poor and proclaiming liberty to captives.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 4, 18, 40, 11, 5, 5, 'to preach the gospel to the poor', 'Connection of Healing and Preaching', 'Both passages emphasize healing and preaching to the poor. Luke highlights the anointing for these tasks, while Matthew lists the outcomes of Jesus'' ministry, including preaching to the poor.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 4, 18, 44, 10, 38, 38, 'he hath anointed me to preach', 'Connection of Anointing and Healing', 'Both passages emphasize the anointing of Jesus and his mission to heal and deliver. Luke 4:18 speaks of healing the brokenhearted and setting at liberty, while Acts 10:38 mentions healing all that were oppressed.', 'theme', 0.9299999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 4, 18, 42, 7, 22, 22, NULL, 'Connection of Healing and Preaching', 'Both passages emphasize the ministry of Jesus in healing and preaching to the marginalized. The mention of the blind seeing and the poor receiving the gospel in both verses highlights a consistent theme of restoration and hope.', 'theme', 0.8319999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 4, 18, 44, 26, 18, 18, 'to set at liberty them that are bruised', 'Healing and Deliverance Themes', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of opening eyes and delivering individuals from darkness. Luke 4:18 speaks of healing and liberty, while Acts 26:18 focuses on turning from darkness to light and receiving forgiveness.', 'theme', 0.7829999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 4, 18, 23, 42, 7, 7, NULL, 'Connection of Healing and Liberation', 'Both passages emphasize the themes of opening blind eyes and bringing prisoners out of darkness. This connection highlights a shared mission of healing and liberation.', 'theme', 0.7409999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
